            <p class="text-justify">Note: If the carry-on baggage size is larger than the given dimensions then passengers required to pay additional charges on the final destination. </p>
            <h3>United Airlines Carry-On Baggage Exception Policy:</h3>
            <p class="text-justify">1). As we already told most of the passengers can carry one personal item and one carry-on item on board in the united flights but still there are some exception as per the baggage policy that you must know. </p>
            <p class="text-justify">2). Basic economy tickets come with only one personal item on board as per the United Baggage Policy. </p>
            <p class="text-justify">3). In-case if any passenger bring a full-size carry-on baggage to the gate then, basic economy ticket holder should required to check the bag and the baggage fee at the gate is $25. A passenger can pay the United Checked Baggage Fee by the credit card. </p>
            <p class="text-justify">4). Flyers can also follow the rules of Normal Carry-On Baggage Policy with the basic economy tickets with some exceptions such as flyers who are travelling on the Trans-Atlantic Flights to or from the US, Mexico and Central America and from El Salvador, Panama and South America </p>

            <p class="text-justify">5). Normal Carry-On Baggage Policy also applicable for the customers travelling on Trans-Pacific Flights to or from the United and Members of Mileage Plus Plan too. </p>
            <h3>United Express flights: </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">United Express is the regional partner airlines of the United Airlines and the aircrafts are smaller than the normal United Airlines. That means the room and overhead bin spaces are less for the carry-on bags in the United Express Flights. Sometimes the roller bags and larger carry-on bags also not fit in the overhead bin space of United Express Flights. Here we are also going to describe the policies of baggage for the United Express Flights. </p>
