            <h4>Get Green Tag from Agent to Gate Check Your Bag: </h4>
            <p class="text-justify">On the other hand, if you want to gate-check your baggage then you will also get the green tag at the airport from the agent. Once you will get the green tag then the United Baggage Handles also collect the bags at the end of the Jet Bridge during the boarding time. Once you reach on your destination you can pick your bag during and start the process of baggage claim. </p>
            <p class="text-justify">When you are travelling in the United Express Flights, and you have any kind of medications stuff then you must board these items as the personal item or carry=on item. Passengers can also pack the personal vaporizers and e-cigarettes in smaller carry-on bag or personal item. </p>
            <h3>Fragile items: </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">On the other hand, if you are travelling with any kind of fragile or bulky item that is too bulky for travel as the checked bag then you need to buy particular ticket for the team. </p>
            <h3>Things to Keep in Mind about Carry-On Baggage United Airlines for Smoother Experience: </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">Facing any kind of difficulty at the security gate is the worst situation for the flyers and that’s why keeping some facts about the United Airlines Baggage Policy is the nice idea to avoid any hassles and making your travelling experience smoother.  Some baggage items required special attention of the flyers because if they don’t know about the policies for these items then they may need to pay higher amount of money for the baggage of these items. </p>
            <h3>Gels, Liquids and Aerosols: </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">There are some rules and restrictions of Transportation Security Administration for the packing gels, aerosols and liquids in the carry-on baggage of the United Airlines. A traveler must use containers to carry these items with the measure of 3.4 ounces or less. These items must be inside a single quart-size or liter-size clear, sealable bag. This rule is not applicable for liquids such as baby formula and medicine and duty-free liquids in the carry-on bags. </p>
            <h3>Powder Based Substances: </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">If you are travelling with any item that is in the form of powder then keep the item in your checked bag not in the carry-on bag for the smooth on-boarding. As per the rules of TSA, customers who are travelling to or within the United States not allowed to pack powder based stuff greater than 12 fluid ounces in the carry-on bags and that’s why it must pack in the checked bag. This rule is not applicable for the medically prescribed powders, medicines, baby formula and duty free powders. Passengers can also visit at the portal of DHS to know more about the rules. </p>

            <h3>Musical instruments As Carry-On Bags:</h3>
            <p class="text-justify">A passenger can easily carry the musical instruments as the carry-on bag such as violin, guitar or other small stuff in the hard case. These items will be counted as the carry-on bag and must fit in the overhead bin space of the United Airlines. </p>
            <h3>Nursing Mothers: </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">United airlines baggage policies are not strict for the nursing mothers and passengers can bring a breast pump as one of the special items. However, for more information, passengers can also visit at the “Travelling with Children” page of the United Airlines. </p>
            <h2>United Airlines Checked Baggage Rules &amp; Terms to Know:</h2>
            <p class="text-justify">Checked baggage policy of <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/united-airlines-flights-reservations.aspx">United Airlines Booking</a> is also depending on the destination and fare class of the passenger. Sometimes you may need to pay for the checked bags but sometimes you may also save your money on the checked bag. Passengers can also use the United Airlines Baggage Calculator before planning for the trip. </p>
            <h3>What is the Costing of Checked Bag in United Air?</h3>
            <p class="text-justify">It depends on your fare type and your destination and for this you need to sign in to your Mileage Plus Account to explore the upcoming trip information and the baggage details too. </p>
            <h3>Weight and Size Limit for United Airlines Checked Baggage:</h3>
            <p class="text-justify">Most of the standard checked baggage measurement in the United Airlines must not crossed 62 inches dimensions. Weight of the checked bag depends on the cabin and premier status at the time of check-in. You can carry maximum size checked bag and maximum weight checked bags in your cabin as per the Mileage plus Status. Airline also applies the larger limits in many cases. </p>
            <h3>Weight Limit of United Checked Bags:</h3>
            <p class="text-justify">1). If you are travelling with the United Economy Tickets then the weight limit of one checked bag is 50 Pounds</p>
            <p class="text-justify">2). On the other hand, if you are travelling in the United First, Business and Polaris Business Class then the weight limit of United Checked bag is 70 Pounds. </p>
            <p class="text-justify">3). Weight limit for the united checked baggage status can also increase as per the MileagePlus Plan Status. </p>
            <p class="text-justify">4). If you have any of these status in the MileagePlus Plan of United Air; Premier Silver, Premier Gold, Premier Platinum, Premier 1K® and Star Alliance™ Gold and you are travelling in the United Economy then you can increase the weight limited of checked baggage up to 70 pounds. </p>
            <h4>Check Your Bag on Time: </h4>
            <p class="text-justify">You must know about the latest time for the checked bag at the departure airport. If you cross the deadline of checked baggage timing then the airline not precede your bags in the checking process.  A passenger also received the claim check for each checked bag and you must keep the receipts until you collect your all bags at the final destination. United Airlines check bags between the origin and the final destinations listed on the tickets. </p>
            <h3>Exception of Checked Bag Charges to Know:</h3>
            <p class="text-justify">1). some customers don’t have need to pay any kind of service charges on the check bags. This rule is only applicable for the United and United Express Operated Flights when you checked the bags. A passenger can check the eligibility at the United Airlines Official Site for the different types of exemptions. </p>
            <p class="text-justify">2). Active US Military Personnel and their dependents also get so many exceptions in the baggage policy for the checked bags services charges. </p>
            <p class="text-justify">3). For personal travel in all class of services they can carry 3 checked bags with maximum 62 inches dimensions and 70 lbs weight. </p>
            <p class="text-justify">4). For Military Dependent with travel orders in all class of services 2 checked bags allowed with maximum 62 inches dimensions and 70 lbs weight. </p>
            <p class="text-justify">5). For official business, in all class of services 5 checked bags allowed with maximum 115 inches dimensions and 100 lbs weight. </p>
            <h2>Prepay For United Airlines Checked Bags: </h2>
            <p class="text-justify">For the convenience of the passengers united airlines also offer the feature of prepaying for the checked bags in the United Airlines and United Express Flights. You need to select destination and pay the checked baggage fee on prepay mode to save more. Prepay checked bag is the right opportunity for the flyers because with this they can complete the check-in process fast. They don’t have need to rush at the airport for the checked baggage fee if they already pay it. However, this option is not accessible for the oversized and overweight bags in the United Airlines. </p>
            <h3>How to Prepay for the Checked Bags in United Airlines :</h3>
            <p class="text-justify">1). Visit on the United Airlines Reservations Official Site</p>
            <p class="text-justify">2). Enter the Reservations Number or Confirmation Number</p>
            <p class="text-justify">3). Choose “Prepay Bag” Tab</p>
            <p class="text-justify">4). Add the Information related to baggage and ticket</p>
            <p class="text-justify">5). Select ‘Continue to Payment” </p>
            <h2 class="text-justify">Pack Less and Save More in United Airlines Baggage: </h2>
            <p class="text-justify">1). When you are a flyer who is always thinking to save money for the travel goals then you should pack less to save more for the baggage., </p>
            <p class="text-justify">2). Extra baggage only create a big burden of more money on the travelers and that’s why they must choose the baggage that is necessary only for them. </p>
            <p class="text-justify">3). Always double check the baggage policy of the airline to avoid any kind of hassles because these things only create the possibilities of higher amount of baggage at the time of security check at the ate. </p>
            <p class="text-justify">4). United Airlines Basic Economy Tickets are ideal for those flyers who only want to fly with the one personal item. When you are not travelling with more baggage or checked bags then you can buy the tickets of basic economy to save more. </p>
            <p class="text-justify">5). United Airlines Polaris Business Class comes with extra-ordinary baggage advantages for the flyers and with these advantages they can explore more baggage and travel opportunities. You will also get the priority during the security check and check-in. </p>
